  description = 'The athlete waits for a live cue (ball arrives after turn or name call), selects the correct answer, performs the movement response, and resets before the next rep. The rep counts only when the athlete reacts to the real stimulus rather than guessing early.',
  card_summary = '360 Awareness Catch with Safe Twist is a reaction-time-reduction drill for rotational visual reacquisition and catch response. Use it when the goal is faster stimulus recognition, cleaner first movement, and safer reset behavior without turning reaction work into conditioning.',
  coach_language = 'Primary subrole: perception_action_reactive_movement. Coach 360 Awareness Catch with Safe Twist as a quality-first reaction drill: define the cue, remove ambiguous starts, require a clean answer, and rest long enough that speed, accuracy, posture, and safety stay intact.',
